                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#iv #iir #iiv" facs="001 002"/><title type="incomplete" ref="LIT2835RepCh119"/>, incomplete at the beginning. Written in a different hand.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a2"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#186v #187r #187v #188r #188v #189r #189v #190r #190v #191r #191v #192r #192v" facs="189 190 191 192 193 194 195"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2835RepCh119"/>. Written in a different hand. Incipit:<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምከ፡ ምስለ፡ ስመ፡ ልዑል፡ ዘተሳተፈ።</foreign></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e1"><desc>A bookmark made of parchment appears between <locus target="#37 #38" facs="040"/></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a3"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#1r" facs="003">f. 1r and passim</locus> mention the owner Wälättä Mädḫən, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ መድኅን፡</foreign></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a4"><desc><locus target="#7r and passim"/> mention <persName ref="PRS1822IHA"/></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a5"><desc><locus target="#8v #96r" facs="011 098"/>Prayer mentions Wäldä Mikaʾel, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>, perhaps the late husband of the owner</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a6"><desc><locus target="#69v" facs="072"/> mentions her father (without mentioning his name) and her mother Wälättä Mikaʾel, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a7"><desc><locus target="#96r" facs="098"/> mentions her father Wäldä Ṣädəq <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ጸድቅ፡</foreign>, her mother Wälättä Mikaʾel,  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>, the soul of Wäldä Mikaʾel, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>, and her children Gäbrä Waḥəd, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ዋሕድ፡</foreign>, Säyfä Śəllase, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰይፈ፡ ሥላሴ፡</foreign>, Wäldä ʾAmanuʾel,
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ አማኑኤል፡</foreign>, ʾƎḫtä Mikaʾel, <foreign xml:lang="gez">እኅተ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>, Ṣəlalotä Dəngəl, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጽላሎተ፡ ድንግል፡</foreign>, Məśṭirä Śəllase, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምሥጢረ፡ ሥላሴ፡</foreign>. Cf. the list on <locus target="#185v" facs="188"/>, mentions the souls of Wäldä Mikaʾel,
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign> and Gäbrä Wäld, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ወልድ፡</foreign></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a8"><desc type="ScribalSignature"><locus target="#185v" facs="188"/> mentions the scribe Zärʾä Yoḥännəs <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘርአ፡ ዮሐንስ፡</foreign></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e2"><desc><locus target="#"/> quires 2–7, 9–14, and 17–19.</desc></item>
